Subject: CVE-2024-45627: Apache Linkis Metadata Query Service JDBC: JDBC
 Datasource Module with Mysql has file read vulnerability 

Severity: important

Affected versions:

- Apache Linkis Metadata Query Service JDBC 1.5.0 before 1.7.0

Description:

In Apache Linkis <1.7.0, due to the lack of effective filtering
of parameters, an attacker configuring malicious Mysql JDBC parameters in the DataSource Manager Module will 

allow the attacker to read arbitrary files from the Linkis server. Therefore, the parameters in the Mysql JDBC URL should be blacklisted. This attack requires the attacker to obtain an authorized account from Linkis before it can be carried out. Versions of Apache Linkis < 1.6.0 will be affected. 
We recommend users upgrade the version of Linkis to version 1.7.0.

Credit:

Le1a (reporter)

References:

https://linkis.apache.org
